TITLE: Struct-to-Table Mapping with Go-Gorp
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define Go struct types and map them to database tables using Go-Gorp. Demonstrates different approaches to column mapping including using struct tags to rename fields, set primary keys, and ignore fields during mapping.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kubesphere/kubesphere/blob/master/vendor/github.com/go-gorp/gorp/v3/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
type Invoice struct {
    Id       int64
    Created  int64
    Updated  int64
    Memo     string
    PersonId int64
}

type Person struct {
    Id      int64
    Created int64
    Updated int64
    FName   string
    LName   string
}

// Example of using tags to alias fields to column names
// The 'db' value is the column name
//
// A hyphen will cause gorp to skip this field, similar to the
// Go json package.
//
// This is equivalent to using the ColMap methods:
//
//   table := dbmap.AddTableWithName(Product{}, "product")
//   table.ColMap("Id").Rename("product_id")
//   table.ColMap("Price").Rename("unit_price")
//   table.ColMap("IgnoreMe").SetTransient(true)
//
// You can optionally declare the field to be a primary key and/or autoincrement
//
type Product struct {
    Id         int64     `db:"product_id, primarykey, autoincrement"`
    Price      int64     `db:"unit_price"`
    IgnoreMe   string    `db:"-"`
}
```

