TITLE: Handling Error Stacktraces in Go
DESCRIPTION: Example of handling errors from the go-errors/errors package in a main function. Shows how to check if an error matches a specific error using errors.Is and how to print the error stack trace.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kubesphere/kubesphere/blob/master/vendor/github.com/go-errors/errors/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
    "crashy"
    "fmt"
    "github.com/go-errors/errors"
)

func main() {
    err := crashy.Crash()
    if err != nil {
        if errors.Is(err, crashy.Crashed) {
            fmt.Println(err.(*errors.Error).ErrorStack())
        } else {
            panic(err)
        }
    }
}
```

