TITLE: Concurrent Mapping of Slice in Go
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to concurrently map a slice using both the standard library and the 'conc' package. The 'conc' version simplifies the implementation using the iter.Map function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kubesphere/kubesphere/blob/master/vendor/github.com/sourcegraph/conc/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func concMap(
    input []int,
    f func(int) int,
) []int {
    res := make([]int, len(input))
    var idx atomic.Int64

    var wg sync.WaitGroup
    for i := 0; i < 10; i++ {
        wg.Add(1)
        go func() {
            defer wg.Done()

            for {
                i := int(idx.Add(1) - 1)
                if i >= len(input) {
                    return
                }

                res[i] = f(input[i])
            }
        }()
    }
    wg.Wait()
    return res
}
```

