TITLE: Processing Slice Elements with Static Goroutine Pool in Go
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to process each element of a slice using a static pool of goroutines. The 'conc' version significantly simplifies the implementation using the iter.ForEach function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kubesphere/kubesphere/blob/master/vendor/github.com/sourcegraph/conc/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
func process(values []int) {
    feeder := make(chan int, 8)

    var wg sync.WaitGroup
    for i := 0; i < 10; i++ {
        wg.Add(1)
        go func() {
            defer wg.Done()
            for elem := range feeder {
                handle(elem)
            }
        }()
    }

    for _, value := range values {
        feeder <- value
    }
    close(feeder)
    wg.Wait()
}
```

