TITLE: Updating Git Tags with Bash Script
DESCRIPTION: The shell script is used to convert lightweight tags to signed tags in a Git repository, preserving commit date, name, and email address. It requires the bash shell and Git to be installed. Users must specify the tag name as a parameter when running the script.
