TITLE: Retrieving Route Variable Names with Gorilla Mux in Go
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using the `GetVarNames()` method on a named route (`r.Get("article")`) to retrieve a slice of strings containing the names of all variables defined in the route's host ('domain'), path ('group', 'item_id'), and queries ('some_data1', 'some_data2'). This helps identify the required parameters for URL generation methods like `URL()`.
