TITLE: Creating Resource Quota Script in KubeSphere
DESCRIPTION: This shell script creates a resource quota with specified limits for various resources including CPU, memory, and storage. It applies the quota to a specified namespace by creating a YAML configuration through kubectl.
SOURCE: https://github.com/kubesphere/kubesphere/blob/master/hack/custom-boilerplate.go.txt#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
cat <<EOF | kubectl create -f -
apiVersion: quota.kubesphere.io/v1alpha2
kind: ResourceQuota
metadata:
  name: quota
  namespace: default
spec:
  quota:
    hard:
      limits.cpu: "2"
      limits.memory: 2Gi
      pods: "500"
      requests.storage: 10Gi
      count/deployments.apps: "10"
  resources:
    - resourceName: limits.cpu
      hard: "2"
    - resourceName: limits.memory
      hard: 2Gi
    - resourceName: pods
      hard: "500"
    - resourceName: requests.storage
      hard: 10Gi
    - resourceName: count/deployments.apps
      hard: "10"
EOF
```

